    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>your letters are always so acceptable as never to need apology. I wish much that
                        <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> had
                        <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0086">Saxo Grammaticus</title>
                    </bibl>
                    for with that is printed <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0087">Torfæus’s
                            hist. of the orcades</title>
                    </bibl>: I will lend him mine <sic>if not be
                        got.</sic> also <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0088">olaus
                            magnus</title>
                    </bibl> which treats much of northern nations. I shall
                    soon write to him again to urge his visit next summer to <placeName ref="pl0700">the
                        Shetlands</placeName>; in terms I hope he will not decline. Those isles shd
                    go with the other to complete our plan.</p>
                <p>If you can pick up anything historical ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    <placeName ref="pl0714">Bute</placeName> its Castles of <placeName ref="pl0619">Rosay</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="pl1186">Kaymes</placeName> or of
                        <placeName ref="pl0719">the isle of arran</placeName> it will be most
                    welcome.</p>
                <p>I scarce know that to say about <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0089">y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> M.S.</title>
                    </bibl> The steed is stolen,
                    the foundation of depopulation is Laid in <placeName ref="pl0708">the
                        isles</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="pl0711">Highlands</placeName>; &amp;
                    I fear it will be too late to discuss on what might have been done. But still
                    would it come readily it might merit perusal.</p>
                <p>Be so good as to transmit the inclosed &amp; return me the answer from <placeName ref="pe0022">the Doctor</placeName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, Dear Sir, <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> very faithfull
                        H. Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1773.</dateline>
            </div>
